# PROJECT MASTER CONTEXT

## Project Overview
- **Name:** [اسم مشروعك]
- **Stack:** Next.js 16 (App Router) + Supabase (PostgreSQL) + Drizzle ORM / Prisma
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (SSR-aware)

---

## Architecture Rules

### Folder Structure
src/
├── app/ # App Router pages & layouts
│ ├── (auth)/ # Auth route group
│ ├── (dashboard)/ # Protected route group
│ └── api/ # API routes
├── components/
│ ├── ui/ # Reusable UI components
│ └── features/ # Feature-specific components
├── lib/
│ ├── supabase/ # Supabase clients (server/client)
│ ├── db/ # ORM schema & queries
│ └── utils/ # Helper functions
├── hooks/ # Custom React hooks
├── types/ # Global TypeScript types
└── actions/ # Server Actions

### Component Rules
- Max **200 lines** per component file — split if longer
- Use **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when needed
- Prefer **Server Actions** over API routes for mutations
- Export one component per file, named same as filename

---

## Code Style

- **TypeScript:** Always define explicit return types for functions
- **Imports:** Use `@/` alias, not relative paths like `../../`
- **Async/Await:** Never use `.then()` chains — always `async/await`
- **Error Handling:** Wrap every async operation in try/catch
- **Variables:** `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment needed
- **No `any`:** Never use `any` type — use `unknown` or define proper types

---

## Naming Conventions

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | PascalCase | `UserProfile.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase + use | `useAuthSession.ts` |
| Server Actions | camelCase + Action | `createPostAction.ts` |
| DB Tables | snake_case | `user_profiles` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase + T/I | `TUser`, `IPost` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_FILE_SIZE` |

---

## Security Rules

- NEVER expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to the client
- NEVER log passwords, tokens, or sensitive data
- ALWAYS validate inputs with **Zod** before processing
- ALWAYS use parameterized queries — no string interpolation in SQL
- Server Actions must verify **auth session** before any DB operation

---

## Response Format for AI

When making any change:
1. State **what** you're changing and **why**
2. Show only the **modified sections**, not the entire file
3. If adding a new dependency, mention the install command
4. Flag any **breaking changes** explicitly
5. Keep responses concise — no filler text
